The operatives of Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps, Lagos State Command have recovered 3,896 litres of petroleum product in the Badagry Local Government Area of Lagos State. This was disclosed via NSCDC ‘s Twitter handle on Tuesday.  Pictures of the recovered products were shared with the caption, “As the fight against Illegal oil bunkery activities, oil theft and Illegal dealings in petroleum products continue, the operatives of NSCDC Lagos State Command storms Badagry Local Government Area, recovers 3,896 liters of petroleum product.” 